headline: Trump signs global 10% tariff order hours after Supreme Court strikes down 'reciprocal tariffs'
description: After the US Supreme Court ruled that President Donald Trump had exceeded his authority by imposing tariffs on virtually all US trading partners, Trump earlier said he would circumvent the decision and use another law to impose uniform tariffs, which he then said he signed off on later on Friday, 'effective almost immediately.'

headline: French activist's death ignites Italy's far-right circles
Newsom and Pritzker demand refunds after US court tosses Trump tariffs
UNRWA's cash flow problems force it to scale back its services in the Middle East
description: The United Nations agency for Palestinian refugees' schools and health centers have had to reduce their services by 20% due to insufficient funding. Its donors have come under pressure from the US and Israel, both of which have accused UNRWA of collusion with Hamas.

headline: CEO of Mistral AI says warnings about extreme risks of artificial intelligence are often 'distraction tactics'
description: Arthur Mensch stands out for his views on the risks posed by artificial intelligence, which have been voiced by OpenAI CEO Sam Altman and Anthropic CEO Dario Amodei.

headline: US freeskier Ferreira wins halfpipe gold: 'I'm finally in the history books'
description: 31-year-old Alex Ferreira won halfpipe silver at the 2018 Pyeongchang Games and followed up with bronze in Beijing four years later.

headline: In legendary Swiss village of Sils-Maria, the Chesa Marchetta hotel blends art with the art of living
description: Gallerists Iwan and Manuela Wirth chose the Swiss canton of Grisons to open their second location. They entrusted the restoration of this former mountain inn to architect Luis Laplace, who took care to remain faithful to the rustic spirit of the place while punctuating it with works of art.

Gaza's local authorities massively underreported deaths, says international research team
description: The first independent field study on Gaza to not involve local authorities, published in The Lancet Global Health on Wednesday, concludes that the number of violent deaths linked to the conflict has been underreported by about 35%.

headline: From the Château de Versailles to the Elysée, the unshakable Catherine Pégard
description: Against all odds and well beyond her legal term, the former journalist who became adviser to President Nicolas Sarkozy held on as head of the Château de Versailles for 12 years. Forced out of her position in 2024, the skillful and tenacious Catherine Pégard quickly found a seat at the Elysée as culture adviser. Now, rumors suggest she could replace Rachida Dati, currently running for Paris City Hall, if she gives up her ministerial post.

headline: Xavier Dolan, filmmaker: "Where does the idea that artists should 'stay out of politics' come from?"
description: A controversy is stirring at this year's Berlinale. At their opening press conference, the jury members declined to comment on the situation in Palestine, with their president, Wim Wenders, arguing that cinema should 'stay out of politics.' Canadian director Xavier Dolan responds to him in an op-ed for Le Monde.

headline: 'The fall of the cumbersome Jack Lang is seen as providential for France's political spectrum, which remains paralyzed by his cultural legacy'
Rejecting political violence
Paul Magnette, political scientist: 'If Trump's camp felt superior, why try and divide Europe?'
